00:41:37,729 --> 00:41:39,731
Billy, I'm changin'
yer name to Catfish!

1037
00:41:39,731 --> 00:41:42,266
You all mouth and no brains!

1038
00:41:42,266 --> 00:41:43,501
[MAV]
He's nuts!

1039
00:41:43,501 --> 00:41:43,901
[TALLY]
Yeah.

1040
00:41:43,901 --> 00:41:46,104
[MAV]
Let's get the hell outta here!

1041
00:41:46,104 --> 00:41:48,266
[TALLY] We're not leavin'
without that briefcase!

1042
00:42:11,562 --> 00:42:14,098
Okay... Okay...

1043
00:42:14,098 --> 00:42:15,395
Let's go.

1044
00:42:22,774 --> 00:42:27,478
[ELMER] Them stars sure
are beautiful tonight.

1045
00:42:27,478 --> 00:42:32,750
Ain't no lights from
the city to drown them out.

1046
00:42:32,750 --> 00:42:35,879
Not a soul around for miles.

1047
00:42:38,156 --> 00:42:40,058
You know, before the fire,

1048
00:42:40,058 --> 00:42:43,494
there was a porch on the back.

1049
00:42:43,494 --> 00:42:46,486
That view's even better
from the east.

1050
00:42:49,500 --> 00:42:52,834
Wish the view's
all I lost that night.

1051
00:42:54,739 --> 00:42:57,141
Yer Daddy give me the money

1052
00:42:57,141 --> 00:42:59,744
to put this place back
just the way it was.

1053
00:42:59,744 --> 00:43:04,282
Down to the square head nails
and the framin' lumber.

1054
00:43:04,282 --> 00:43:08,150
Give me the money to make this
place profitable again, too.

1055
00:43:11,422 --> 00:43:15,188
5... Somethin' missin' here,
though, ain't there?

1056
00:43:27,105 --> 00:43:28,834
Hey, Uncle Elmer.

1057
00:43:32,376 --> 00:43:34,640
You have a very
beautiful family.

1058
00:43:36,380 --> 00:43:42,649
Sure do. Sure do.

1059
00:43:46,057 --> 00:43:48,993
[ELMER]
Hey, boys, look what I found!

1060
00:43:48,993 --> 00:43:51,655
This was in the
closet upstairs.

1061
00:43:52,663 --> 00:43:55,466
I-1 think, uh, this might
be what you're lookin' for.

1062
00:43:55,466 --> 00:43:58,026
It is, Uncle Elmer.
Thank you, thank you.

1063
00:44:04,342 --> 00:44:05,176
All right, well,

1064
00:44:05,176 --> 00:44:07,845
you made it to
your Uncle Elmer's.

1065
00:44:07,845 --> 00:44:09,247
He is an original, isn't he?

1066
00:44:09,247 --> 00:44:10,348
Colt!

1067
00:44:10,348 --> 00:44:12,083
[COLT]
I know, I know, I know,

1068
00:44:12,083 --> 00:44:14,385
both his oars do not
reach the water,

1069
00:44:14,385 --> 00:44:17,722
but that man is a better
musician than I ever was.

1070
00:44:17,722 --> 00:44:19,824
I promise you that.

1071
00:44:19,824 --> 00:44:21,726
Now, I want you to
go to the address

1072
00:44:21,726 --> 00:44:23,761
on that little piece
of paper in the case--

1073
00:44:23,761 --> 00:44:25,263
follow it to your Aunt Zelda's.

1074
00:44:25,263 --> 00:44:26,864
If she is still there,

1075
00:44:26,864 --> 00:44:28,766
she will know exactly
what you need to do next.

1076
00:44:28,766 --> 00:44:30,501
If she is not...

1077
00:44:30,501 --> 00:44:32,770
...you're screwed! [laughs]

1078
00:44:32,770 --> 00:44:36,040
Nah, nah, she'll be there.
Big Devil, out.

1079
00:44:36,040 --> 00:44:40,945
Zelda! Hell, I thought she's
in jail down in Columbia!

1080
00:44:40,945 --> 00:44:42,747
Maybe she got parole?

1081
00:44:42,747 --> 00:44:45,449
She castrated a federale
with a lawn dart.

1082
00:44:45,449 --> 00:44:47,185
Pretty sure parole
was outta play.

1083
00:44:47,185 --> 00:44:48,753
[sighs] I tell you one thing,

1084
00:44:48,753 --> 00:44:51,522
if Zelda's anything
like she used to be,

1085
00:44:51,522 --> 00:44:54,058
ain't no tellin' what
you boys are rollin' into.

1086
00:44:54,058 --> 00:44:56,394
Keep your head on a swivel--

1087
00:44:56,394 --> 00:44:59,030
try not to get shot!

1088
00:44:59,030 --> 00:44:59,697
That's great.

1089
00:44:59,697 --> 00:45:01,199
Will do, Uncle Elmer. Thank you.

1090
00:45:01,199 --> 00:45:02,066
Thank you.

1091
00:45:02,066 --> 00:45:03,868
Thank you for everything.

1092
00:45:03,868 --> 00:45:06,604
[ELMER] You boys take care,
I... 1 put you some, uh...

1093
00:45:06,604 --> 00:45:09,407
...some deviled hams and
some crackers in here.

1094
00:45:09,407 --> 00:45:11,375
That'll travel good for ya.

1095
00:45:11,375 --> 00:45:13,277
l appreciate it. Thank you.

1096
00:45:13,277 --> 00:45:15,613
All right, keep between
the ditches.

1097
00:45:15,613 --> 00:45:17,138
[TALLY chuckles]
Okay.

1098
00:45:21,052 --> 00:45:22,451
Hey, Uncle Elmer.

1099
00:45:24,088 --> 00:45:25,623
Catch you on the way back?

1100
00:45:25,623 --> 00:45:27,387
Ya know, that'd be good.

1101
00:45:29,060 --> 00:45:32,655
Maybe then you boys can
tell me what you wanna do.

1102
00:45:34,599 --> 00:45:36,761
Careful out there now!

1103
00:45:38,169 --> 00:45:40,338
Hey, what ya think
he meant by that?

1104
00:45:40,338 --> 00:45:41,772
[TALLY]
I don't know.

1105
00:45:41,772 --> 00:45:43,741
Maybe he thinks that, uh,

1106
00:45:43,741 --> 00:45:48,012
we'll give him money like
Dad did with our inheritance.

1107
00:45:48,012 --> 00:45:50,181
There'd be worse ways
to spend it.

1108
00:45:50,181 --> 00:45:52,316
Points to Pop, man.

1109
00:45:52,316 --> 00:45:54,910
Yeah, whatever.
Let's get outta here.

1110
00:45:56,988 --> 00:45:59,523
Ignition, dumbass.

1111
00:45:59,523 --> 00:46:00,786
[TALLY]
Yeah.

1112
00:46:04,295 --> 00:46:09,290
>

1113
00:46:42,700 --> 00:46:45,469
[MAV] The hell is this?
Some kind of convent?

1114
00:46:45,469 --> 00:46:46,470
[TALLY]
What?

1115
00:46:46,470 --> 00:46:48,172
[MAYV] Bro. What if they're
giving Aunt Zelda

1116
00:46:48,172 --> 00:46:49,901
some kind of exorcism?

1117
00:46:52,176 --> 00:46:54,412
[TALLY]
Aunt Zelda must be sick.

1118
00:46:54,412 --> 00:46:56,013
[MAV]
Why? What makes you say that?

1119
00:46:56,013 --> 00:46:58,209
This is where Mom came to die.

1120
00:46:59,583 --> 00:47:02,153
[TALLY]
Now, did we learn our lesson?

1121
00:47:02,153 --> 00:47:04,555
There a doorbell?

1122
00:47:04,555 --> 00:47:05,990
Don't walk in.

1123
00:47:05,990 --> 00:47:08,550
[knocking]

1124
00:47:09,727 --> 00:47:11,495
Aunt Zelda!

1125
00:47:11,495 --> 00:47:12,496
[door creaks]

1126
00:47:12,496 --> 00:47:14,565
Hello?!

1127
00:47:14,565 --> 00:47:18,502
--[NUNS] Reprobates!
--[MAYV, TALLY scream]

1128
00:47:18,502 --> 00:47:20,604
--[NUNS] Reprobates!
--[MAV, TALLY screaming]

1129
00:47:20,604 --> 00:47:22,273
[MAV]
Okay! Okay!

1130
00:47:22,273 --> 00:47:24,375
[TALLY] We're looking
for a woman named Zelda!

1131
00:47:24,375 --> 00:47:25,242
Tattooed!

1132
00:47:25,242 --> 00:47:26,911
[MAV]
She might have a crack pipe!

1133
00:47:26,911 --> 00:47:28,612
[NUN A]
Hey! That'll be enough!

1134
00:47:28,612 --> 00:47:30,781
Get outta here. Go on, get out!

1135
00:47:30,781 --> 00:47:32,550
[NUNS screaming]

1136
00:47:32,550 --> 00:47:34,185
[NUN A]
Go on! You old hens!

1137
00:47:34,185 --> 00:47:35,619
Quit your cacklin"!

1138
00:47:35,619 --> 00:47:37,053
Get!

1139
00:47:37,788 --> 00:47:39,256
What?!

1140
00:47:40,624 --> 00:47:42,259
Aunt Zelda?

1141
00:47:42,259 --> 00:47:46,230
Saw the news about Colt
in the paper.

1142
00:47:46,230 --> 00:47:49,100
Took you little
shits long enough.

1143
00:47:49,100 --> 00:47:49,934
You're a nun?

1144
00:47:49,934 --> 00:47:53,104
[ZELDA] Somethin' wrong
with turnin' over a new leaf?

1145
00:47:53,104 --> 00:47:55,706
[TALLY]
Well, no, uh, I just figured...

1146
00:47:55,706 --> 00:47:58,376
...you ever walked into a church
you'd just burst into flames.

1147
00:47:58,376 --> 00:47:59,710
[MAV chuckles]
Yeah.

1148
00:47:59,710 --> 00:48:00,144
[BOTH laugh]

1149
00:48:00,144 --> 00:48:02,747
[ZELDA]
Funny.

1150
00:48:02,747 --> 00:48:06,584
The sisterhood knows
to err is human,

1151
00:48:06,584 --> 00:48:11,322
but to forgive is divine.

1152
00:48:11,322 --> 00:48:13,124
[MAV] I mean, surely if they
knew everything you've done

1153
00:48:13,124 --> 00:48:14,658
they wouldn't let
you in here, right?

1154
00:48:14,658 --> 00:48:16,594
Ha! Told 'em, they didn't care.

1155
00:48:16,594 --> 00:48:17,962
Everything?

1156
00:48:17,962 --> 00:48:18,796
All of it!

1157
00:48:18,796 --> 00:48:19,563
The sodomy?

1158
00:48:19,563 --> 00:48:20,331
[ZELDA]
Mmm... yep!

1159
00:48:20,331 --> 00:48:21,399
[MAV]
The drug dealers?

1160
00:48:21,399 --> 00:48:22,099
[ZELDA]
Uh-huh.

1161
00:48:22,099 --> 00:48:23,801
The sodomy of drug dealers?

1162
00:48:23,801 --> 00:48:28,406
[ZELDA chuckles]
Every... Every dirty detail,

1163
00:48:28,406 --> 00:48:30,608
1 told 'em, they didn't care.

1164
00:48:30,608 --> 00:48:35,413
I'm guessin'... this
is what you're here for.

1165
00:48:35,413 --> 00:48:36,747
[MAV, TALLY]
Yes!

1166
00:48:36,747 --> 00:48:37,281
[MAV]
Thank you.

1167
00:48:37,281 --> 00:48:39,511
Diddle-wisps here, please.

1168
00:48:50,027 --> 00:48:53,327
These are your momma's ashes.

1169
00:48:54,331 --> 00:48:57,435
[ZELDA]
What Colt treasured this urn...

1170
00:48:57,435 --> 00:49:02,206
He wants you two boys
to mix these ashes with his.

1171
00:49:02,206 --> 00:49:05,335
I don't know, spread 'em
where you will.

1172
00:49:07,311 --> 00:49:08,540
Thank you.

1173
00:49:09,680 --> 00:49:12,049
Do you remember much about her?

1174
00:49:12,049 --> 00:49:13,676
Momma?

1175
00:49:15,352 --> 00:49:18,456
Bits and pieces, really.

1176
00:49:18,456 --> 00:49:20,825
I was six when she died, so...

1177
00:49:20,825 --> 00:49:22,359
Too damn young.

1178
00:49:22,359 --> 00:49:24,395
I was ten.

1179
00:49:24,395 --> 00:49:27,298
Well, if ever there was a woman
destined for sainthood,

1180
00:49:27,298 --> 00:49:28,566
it was your momma.

1181
00:49:28,566 --> 00:49:30,234
[TALLY chuckles]
Well, hey, she'd have to be

1182
00:49:30,234 --> 00:49:32,336
to put up with a guy
like Dad, right?

1183
00:49:32,336 --> 00:49:35,239
[ZELDA] You can think what
you want, but he loved her.

1184
00:49:35,239 --> 00:49:39,143
He was never, never
the same after she died.

1185
00:49:39,143 --> 00:49:41,145
Neither were we.

1186
00:49:41,145 --> 00:49:43,013
We needed our father around,

1187
00:49:43,013 --> 00:49:45,049
not somebody that
pretended to be one

1188
00:49:45,049 --> 00:49:46,217
just when it suited him.

1189
00:49:46,217 --> 00:49:48,486
Hey, you watch yourself.

1190
00:49:48,486 --> 00:49:52,656
Do you know that, uh, the last
two weeks Mom was here,

1191
00:49:52,656 --> 00:49:53,991
he wouldn't bring
us to see her?

1192
00:49:53,991 --> 00:49:54,925
Now you wait a minute--

1193
00:49:54,925 --> 00:49:58,562
Couldn't bring his own boys
to see their dying mother!

1194
00:49:58,562 --> 00:50:02,533
No, no, he'd rather play shows
for drunk hillbillies.

1195
00:50:02,533 --> 00:50:03,767
Hell of a guy.

1196
00:50:03,767 --> 00:50:08,572
For your information,
you spoiled little shit,

1197
00:50:08,572 --> 00:50:10,908
Colt didn't bring you here
because your momma

1198
00:50:10,908 --> 00:50:13,611
didn't want you to
see her like that.

1199
00:50:13,611 --> 00:50:15,112
He was honoring her wishes.

1200
00:50:15,112 --> 00:50:17,882
Oh, by abandoning her two boys.

1201
00:50:17,882 --> 00:50:19,283
Is that honoring her wishes?!

1202
00:50:19,283 --> 00:50:20,718
[ZELDA]
Well, he had a rough patch.

1203
00:50:20,718 --> 00:50:21,018
Ha!

1204
00:50:21,018 --> 00:50:22,353
[ZELDA]
He turned it around!

1205
00:50:22,353 --> 00:50:23,020
Please.

1206
00:50:23,020 --> 00:50:25,356
He donated a shitload
of money to this place

1207
00:50:25,356 --> 00:50:27,358
and I wouldn't be
here without him.

1208
00:50:27,358 --> 00:50:30,127
He snuck mein
the pearly gates,

1209
00:50:30,127 --> 00:50:32,129
so to speak.

1210
00:50:32,129 --> 00:50:34,965
Yeah, I see what this is.

1211
00:50:34,965 --> 00:50:37,067
[MAV]
Tally! Tally, hey. Hey, dude!

1212
00:50:37,067 --> 00:50:38,135
Where ya goin"?

1213
00:50:38,135 --> 00:50:39,904
May, this is not a road trip.

1214
00:50:39,904 --> 00:50:42,640
This is the Colt Montana
PR campaign.

1215
00:50:42,640 --> 00:50:45,576
He designed this whole trip
so his buddies can tell us

1216
00:50:45,576 --> 00:50:46,610
how great he was.

1217
00:50:46,610 --> 00:50:47,545
Aunt Zelda.

1218
00:50:47,545 --> 00:50:49,213
[MAV]
Tally!

1219
00:50:49,213 --> 00:50:50,915
--[door slams]
--Aunt Zelda, I'm so sorry.

1220
00:50:50,915 --> 00:50:53,417
I don't know what's
gotten into him.

1221
00:50:53,417 --> 00:50:57,121
Ya know, sometimes when we...
lose those we love,

1222
00:50:57,121 --> 00:51:00,591
we direct that pain and anger

1223
00:51:00,591 --> 00:51:03,894
towards the loved ones
that we still have with us.

1224
00:51:03,894 --> 00:51:06,096
[MAV]
Yeah, could be.

1225
00:51:06,096 --> 00:51:07,965
Or maybe he's just an asshole.

1226
00:51:07,965 --> 00:51:10,601
[MAY laughs]

1227
00:51:10,601 --> 00:51:13,571
You are right about that.

1228
00:51:13,571 --> 00:51:14,738
Let's watch it.

1229
00:51:14,738 --> 00:51:16,604
Oh, okay.

1230
00:51:17,274 --> 00:51:19,109
[COLT]
So, you found your Aunt Zelda,

1231
00:51:19,109 --> 00:51:20,177
which means she's still a nun.

1232
00:51:20,177 --> 00:51:22,813
Now that there, boys, is
a miracle on its own right.

1233
00:51:22,813 --> 00:51:24,181
Amen!

1234
00:51:24,181 --> 00:51:26,483
[COLT]
All right, from here on out,

1235
00:51:26,483 --> 00:51:28,519
I want you to travel
to Big Jake's.

1236
00:51:28,519 --> 00:51:29,787
Directions are in the box.

1237
00:51:29,787 --> 00:51:31,655
You're lookin'
for Jake Fillmore.

1238
00:51:31,655 --> 00:51:33,089
Talk at ya later.

1239
00:51:34,592 --> 00:51:36,927
Jake Fillmore.

1240
00:51:36,927 --> 00:51:41,498
1 do hope you boys find
what you're lookin' for.

1241
00:51:41,498 --> 00:51:44,201
[phone rings]

1242
00:51:44,201 --> 00:51:45,269
[TALLY]
I'm done, Ward!

1243
00:51:45,269 --> 00:51:46,537
What do you mean "done"?

1244
00:51:46,537 --> 00:51:47,471
I mean done.

1245
00:51:47,471 --> 00:51:48,939
I'm tired of Dad
jerkin' us around.

1246
00:51:48,939 --> 00:51:50,107
I don't care about the money.

1247
00:51:50,107 --> 00:51:51,508
I'm not calling
about the money.

1248
00:51:51,508 --> 00:51:54,178
Your, um... your
friends at the SEC

1249
00:51:54,178 --> 00:51:56,146
gave me a jingle this morning.

1250
00:51:56,146 --> 00:51:59,683
Said you owe a shit ton of
cash in the next 48 hours

1251
00:51:59,683 --> 00:52:02,019
or you're officially a fugitive.

1252
00:52:02,019 --> 00:52:03,320
Yeah. I know that, Ward.

1253
00:52:03,320 --> 00:52:04,655
[WARD]
Don't mean to be a gadfly,

1254
00:52:04,655 --> 00:52:06,290
but maybe now isn't the time

1255
00:52:06,290 --> 00:52:10,027
to let your foolish pride get
in the way of saving your ass.

1256
00:52:10,027 --> 00:52:12,563
Well, hey, prison's gotta be
better than this, doesn't it?

1257
00:52:12,563 --> 00:52:16,500
[WARD] I wouldn't know.
Ask Zelda. [laughs]

1258
00:52:16,500 --> 00:52:17,801
How'd you know we
were at Zelda's?

1259
00:52:17,801 --> 00:52:20,037
Oh, well, I watch
the psychic channel,

1260
00:52:20,037 --> 00:52:21,572
you know that.

1261
00:52:21,572 --> 00:52:24,742
Oh, seriously, I, uh, figured
your Dad would send you

1262
00:52:24,742 --> 00:52:26,510
to collect your mum's ashes.

1263
00:52:26,510 --> 00:52:27,978
All else okay?

1264
00:52:27,978 --> 00:52:29,079
Yeah, I'm fine.

1265
00:52:29,079 --> 00:52:31,749
[WARD] Listen, mate, um,
don't be stupid.

1266
00:52:31,749 --> 00:52:35,586
You can hate Colt as much
as you want, but...

1267
00:52:35,586 --> 00:52:37,521
...keep the bars off
your windows. Mm?

1268
00:52:37,521 --> 00:52:40,157
Fine. I'll keep going, but
I'm not happy about it, Ward.

1269
00:52:40,157 --> 00:52:44,321
Eh, happiness is overrated.
Ha, ha, ha!

1270
00:52:45,663 --> 00:52:46,930
[MAV]
Yo, is everything all right?

1271
00:52:46,930 --> 00:52:49,867
[TALLY sighs] Yeah. Good.

1272
00:52:49,867 --> 00:52:50,934
It's good.

1273
00:52:50,934 --> 00:52:52,336
Where to next?

1274
00:52:52,336 --> 00:52:55,673
[MAV] Dad wants us to see
some guy named Jake Fillmore.

1275
00:52:55,673 --> 00:52:57,608
[TALLY]
Okay, well, uh...

1276
00:52:57,608 --> 00:52:59,743
Our bikes are running
on fumes, so...

1277
00:52:59,743 --> 00:53:02,079
Yeah, you got those credit
cards up and runnin"?

1278
00:53:02,079 --> 00:53:04,381
Uh... you know what,
I don't know what's goin' on.

1279
00:53:04,381 --> 00:53:06,884
The system still
